.TH "omap_dm_timer_write_reg" 9 "omap_dm_timer_write_reg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
omap_dm_timer_write_reg \- write timer registers in posted and non-posted mode
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" omap_dm_timer_write_reg
.BI "(struct omap_dm_timer *timer "  ","
.BI "u32 reg "  ","
.BI "u32 value "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "timer" 12
timer pointer over which write operation is to perform
.IP "reg" 12
lowest byte holds the register offset
.IP "value" 12
data to write into the register
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The posted mode bit is encoded in reg. Note that in posted mode the write
pending bit must be checked. Otherwise a write on a register which has a
pending write will be lost.
